 people shall use it asa reference book and mnemonic aid. I will describe the 18 most important plants that every master of herbology and in the first place every cleric shall know who is willing to ensure the grace of Gods by using the traditional rituals.§($1,>) §§Tayanga\n\nThis mushroom has such a distinctive shape, that it is relatively easy to find it. If you happen to see a big round corm on theforest floor, then you have found the Tayanga mushroom. This corm can reach an impressive bulk. Specimen have been found that were as big as a head of a child. But beware: The corm is extremely poisonous and should only be handled with gloves. The best course of action would be to cut off the corm directly above the earth with a long knife and doesn´t touch it afterwards. Important are only the roots, which could reach up to a cubit into the earth. After one has dug out those roots, they can beprepared for ritualistic usage. They have to be washed, then cut into little pieces and later\
 dried. Mixed with a bit of brimstone, it isthen burned in a ritual to please the God of War and the armies of the realm will have the power of berserks in the next battle. §($2,<,-1) §§
