 people shall use it as a reference book and mnemonic aid. I will describe the 18 most important plants that every master of herbology and in the first place every cleric shall know who is willing to ensure the grace of Gods by using the traditional rituals.§($1,>) §§Kelventari\n\nThe Kelventari plants are to be found much harder in the last years. Supposedly it is because the plants are much-lauded by quacksalvers and charlatans to be a true cure for multiple afflictions. The actual effect of the Kelventari plant in the field of medicine is still highly controversial among the masters of the subject. The ritual use however certainly gives considerable advantages. To find Kalventari plants one should always be geared to water. Interestingly, the Kelventari makes no difference between salt and fresh water of the many rivers and lakes which draw through Tamar.The main thing is that there is water nearby at all. Then the plant can be found easily because the dense nest of thick succulent\
 leaves of luscious green color isrelatively easyto spot.   But then it is necessary to dig out the roots which form thick long corms that are often split directly at the nodality and occasionally reaches one armlength into the ground. For the use during a ritual the roots are used fresh or dried. Cut into small chunks and mixed with plenty of oilthe success of the ritual should be guaranteed. Afterwards the god of war will be gracious-tempered and it can amount to a considerable cure of the armies of your empire.§($2,<,-1) §§
