 people shalluse it as a reference book and mnemonic aid. I will describe the 18 most important plants that every master of herbology and in the first place every cleric shall know who is willing to ensure the grace of Gods by using the traditional rituals.§($1,>) §§Olvar\n\nThis mushroom is easy to recognize and once one found a good place, it is easy to create a huge stockpile. Only the locating turns out to be difficult. The Olvar mushroom with its big flat caps luxuriates in almost every area and this is the problem while looking for it. There are simply no favorite places for this mushroom. First you find it in the middle of a meadow hidden in the long grass. Then luxuriates it almost unnoticeable because of its brown color and the base of a solitary tree, or it is hiding in the shadow of a big foundling.That is why only patience and ready eyes are helpful. The skillful collector is well advised to memorize the location once one has found it. Because although one had harvested\
 them there are still good odds to locate more mushrooms nearby. Like all sorts of mushrooms listed in this work, you need the well tried method of thick-featured chunks, air drying and following pulverization for the use while the invocation of the god of fertility. If the ritual is conducted correctly one can expect a considerable surplus for the next harvest.§($2,<,-1) §§
