 people shall useit as a reference book and mnemonic aid. I will describe the 18 most important plants that every master of herbology and in the first place every cleric shall know who is willing to ensure the grace of Gods by using the traditional rituals.§($1,>) §§Breldiar\n\nThe Breldiar herb can best be found in dense forests. It needs the moist and dark habitat under the dense treetops to prosper. Its inconsiderable stems are populated with little blue blooms all over the summer. Thereby these stems grow from a bunch of small leaves. The whole plant is rather inconsiderable and hence, hard to locate on the forest ground. When one has found it most of the work is already done. Though the tapered slim root is the most important part of the Breldiar herb, you dont have to dig unlike other root plants. Mostly it is sufficient to just pull it out at one fell swoop combined with a little twisting to get the plant completely out of the ground. Then the roots which are very solid will be\
 roasted on open flame and then pulverized.Forthe ritual use they will be burned together with frankincense in a bowl. The resulting haze indeed has a horrible scent but it can thereby make the god of agriculture happy. The result is a slight increase yield of herbal resources in the country.§($2,<,-1) §§
