 people shall use it as a reference book and mnemonic aid. I will describe the 18 most important plants that every master of herbology and in the first place every cleric shall know who is willing to ensure the grace of Gods by using the traditional rituals.§($1,>) §§Bukandas\n\nThe Bukandas also is a plant which is domiciled in the dense forests of Tamar. However it is much easier to locate as the little Breldiar herb. Though it can rarely be found and mostly just a few plants at one spot but its high growth makes it relatively well visible. Thereby a single long stem rises from a bed of leaves sometimes up to height of a man and it rarely splits once or twice. At the end of the stems are big brown seed cases. While the blooms of the Bukandas can be seen for just a short period of time the seed cases remain on the plant almost for the entire year.The seed cases will carefully be stripped off the stem. Thus one can find it again the next year and harvest the seed once again. These\
 seeds will be mixed with some hackled resinwithout any additional preparation and will be scattered on the ground in a wide circle during the invocation of the god. After one successfully finished the ceremony the god of fertility will arrange ample blessing with children in your empire. §($2,<,-1) §§
