 people shall use it asa reference book and mnemonic aid. I will describe the 18 most important plants that every master of herbology and in the first place every cleric shall know who is willing to ensure the grace of Gods by using the traditional rituals.§($1,>) §§Gefnul\n\nThe Gefnul grass is a gorgeous plant with magnificent blooms. Unfortunately it is increasingly harder to find. While it covered entire meadows in the past it became rarer in the last time. The reason for this is still not known by most of the masters of herbology. Nowadays one can find Gefnul grass only in impassable swamps, though the more is the pleasure when one finally found one of the characteristic hassocks on the long and exhausting search and spot the remarkable purple blooms. Fortunately it is sufficient to cut off the major part of the hassock right above the ground with the sickle. If one pays attention not to injure the bloom carrying stems you can be quite sure to spot the grass at the same place the\
 next year. The hassock will be boiled inwater to a stock after adding of pure alcohol which will be poured around the fireplace during the ritual to honor the god of war. If the ritual succeeds the armies of the empire will be considerably healed. §($2,<,-1) §§
