 people shall use it asa reference book and mnemonic aid. I will describe the 18 most important plants that every master of herbology and in the first place every cleric shall know who is willing to ensure the grace of Gods by using the traditional rituals.§($1,>) §§Jegga\n\nThe Jegga plant prospers best on the lowland and on meadows and willows. Thereby it is hard to recognize because its brown branches only grow flatly above the ground. Often the branches are quite widely ramified and one single plant can cover an area of some step lengths to the second. Mostly wild meadows are overgrown with grass so densely that even the well trained eye has considerable difficulties to locate the Jegga. The branches only have some leaves und they carry blue plum-sized fruits from early summer on. These fruits will be thoroughly dried for the ritual use. For the actual use they will be set up with some pure alcohol. Thereby the used jars, which preferably consist of ceramic, have to be kept cool.\
 The resulting extraction will bepouredcautiously into a bright fire during the ritual where upon it burns with a greenish flame. Thereby one should act with considerable caution because the slightest in attention can lead to terrible burns.Once one conducted the ceremony correctly the god of fertility will be well-disposed towards you and your empire and a true wave of births will occur in your country. §($2,<,-1) §§
